metric \[Eta] in any dimension. Flat metrics use the Brauer\[Dash]Weyl (Pauli\
\[Dash]Kronecker) construction; non-flat metrics are reached through a \
vielbein decomposition g = e^T . \[Eta] . e. The package also provides \
